### File Structure
```
MovieTicketing/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── movie_catalog.html
│   ├── movie_details.html
│   ├── showtime_selection.html
│   ├── seat_selection.html
│   ├── booking_confirmation.html
│   ├── booking_history.html
│   └── theater_information.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (movie posters, icons, etc.)
│
└── data/
    ├── movies.txt
    ├── theaters.txt
    ├── showtimes.txt
    ├── seats.txt
    ├── bookings.txt
    └── genres.txt
```

### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It handles routing, data processing, reading and writing to local text files in the `data/` directory, and serves the HTML templates. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic including data management, business logic, and page rendering will be contained here.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the eight pages of the web application. Each file corresponds to one page as specified in the requirements:
  - `dashboard.html`: Dashboard page with featured movies and navigation buttons.
  - `movie_catalog.html`: Movie catalog with search and filter.
  - `movie_details.html`: Detailed movie information.
  - `showtime_selection.html`: Showtimes listing and filtering.
  - `seat_selection.html`: Interactive seat map for seat selection.
  - `booking_confirmation.html`: Booking review and confirmation form.
  - `booking_history.html`: Display of past bookings with filters.
  - `theater_information.html`: Theater details and filtering.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets used by the web pages:
  - `css/styles.css`: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
  - `js/scripts.js`: JavaScript for interactive elements such as seat selection and dynamic filtering.
  - `images/`: Folder for storing movie posters, icons, and other images.

- **data/**  
  Stores all application data in text files as per the specified formats:
  - `movies.txt`: Movie information.
  - `theaters.txt`: Theater details.
  - `showtimes.txt`: Showtimes data.
  - `seats.txt`: Seat layout and status.
  - `bookings.txt`: Booking records.
  - `genres.txt`: Genre definitions.

This structure cleanly separates backend logic, frontend templates, static resources, and data storage, facilitating maintainability and scalability while meeting the project requirements.
